        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_gawyz" xml:lang="os">
                <form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>gawyz</orth></form>
                <form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>gawiz</orth></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>ковер</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>carpet</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>walʒygon kærdægyl gawyz ærytydtoj, gawyzy wælæ ærtæ turkag
                            bazy</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>на весенней траве разостлали ковер, на ковре — три турецкие
                                подушки</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the carpet was spread on the spring grass, and on the carpet there
                                were three Turkish pillows</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"
                            /><biblScope>134</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>styr kæsgon wærdon ræsuǧd aræzt gawyztæj</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>большая кабардинская арба, красиво украшенная коврами</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>large Kabardian cart, beautifully decorated with carpets</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"
                            /><biblScope>142</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Идет из тюрко-монгольской языковой сферы: <mentioned
                        xml:lang="mn"><lang/>
                        <w>kewis, kews</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Ramstedt"/><biblScope>230</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_ЗКВ"/><biblScope>V 81</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="mn"><lang/>
                        <w>kibes</w></mentioned> (<bibl><biblScope>Бурдуков. Русско-монг. словарь,
                            Л., 1935, стр. 122</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="alt"><lang/>
                        <w>käbis</w></mentioned> (ср. <mentioned xml:lang="bo"><lang/>
                        <w>kebs</w></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/>
                        <w>küüz</w>
                        <gloss><q>ковер</q></gloss></mentioned>’. Сюда примыкают и <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ce"><lang/>
                        <w>kuz</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>kuvs</w>
                        <gloss><q>ковер</q></gloss></mentioned>. Исходная форма %i*kebis%i,
                    %i*kawis%i. Допуская перебой %is%i || %ir%i, мы могли иметь %i*kebir%i,
                    %i*kawir%i, что лежит, может быть, в основе <mentioned xml:lang="sla"><lang/>
                        <w>ковер</w></mentioned> (считается неразъясненным).</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It comes from the Turkic-Mongolian language sphere: <mentioned
                        xml:lang="mn"><lang/>
                        <w>kewis, kews</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Ramstedt"/><biblScope>230</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_ЗКВ"/><biblScope>V 81</biblScope></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="mn"><lang/>
                        <w>kibes</w></mentioned>
                            (<bibl><author>Burdukov</author><biblScope>Russian-Mongolian dictionary,
                            Leningrad, 1935, p. 122</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="alt"><lang/>
                        <w>käbis</w></mentioned> (compare with <mentioned xml:lang="bo"><lang/>
                        <w>kebs</w></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="krc-x-balkar"><lang/>
                        <w>küüz</w>
                        <gloss><q>ковер</q></gloss></mentioned>’. <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/>
                        <w>kuz</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>kuvs</w>
                        <gloss><q>carpet</q></gloss></mentioned> are also related. The initial form
                    is %i*kebis%i, %i*kawis%i. Supposing that there was an alternation %is%i ||
                    %ir%i, we could have %i*kebir%i, %i*kawir%i, from which <mentioned
                        xml:lang="sla"><lang/>
                        <w>ковер</w>
                        <gloss><q>carpet</q></gloss></mentioned> might be originated (it is
                    considered unexplained).</etym>
            </entry>
